name: integer_u16_one
description: |
  One is a baseline u16 operand for boundary arithmetic. Adding it to the
  maximum overflows, subtracting it from zero underflows, and dividing it by
  zero exercises integer divide-by-zero handling. It also provides a simple
  value for detecting accidental signed decoding.
format: hex
decode-as: u16-le
tags:
  - "integer"
  - "unsigned-integer"
  - "u16"
  - "one"
  - "overflow"
  - "underflow"
  - "division-by-zero"
  - "baseline"
---
01 00   # 1
